The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, June 21, 2004 				 Signs of our times
																								Autograph Collectors Club of India is the brainchild of a threesome with an unusual hobby of collecting autographs of people who have left a mark in our world. Of the founding members of the club, Santosh Kumar Lahoti is an avid autograph collector, R D Binani a renowned philatelist and Prashant Arora a photographer with an interest in philately. The main objective of the club is to promote this educational and interesting hobby in India and its neighbouring countries. Autographex - 2004 displays the collections of Prashant Arora, Gopal Das Agrawal, Arindam Banerjee, Santosh Kumar Lahoti, Ratan Chand Batia, Samidh Kumar Thakur, Gostha Behari Dey, Dilip Kumar Saha and other members of the club. On display at the exhibition are several kinds of autographs including those on photographs, autographed letters and autographs on sketches, among others. It is a rare exhibition by dint of its unique exhibit of autographs of personalities of the likes of Mother Teresa, Jawaharlal Nehru, Indira Gandhi and Subhash Chandra Bose.																								Event: An exhibition of autographs																								When: Till June 22; 2 pm - 8 pm																								Where: Gaganendra Shilpa Pradarshasala
